Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located in the heart of Downtown Edmonton, Commerce Place offers a prime retail business opportunity. The building is situated between the Art District and Ice District with direct connections to the above ground Pedway System as well the Central LRT Station, Commerce Place provides pivotal connections between Edmonton Transit, the Pedway System and other key downtown buildings. With its glass crown and granite retail pavilion, Commerce Place is a landmark building in Edmonton. Exciting opportunity to join current tenants Starbucks, McDonald's, Subway, Tim Horton's, The Chopped Leaf, Sunterra Market and future Goodlife Fitness.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: A top-tier new development servicing the rapidly expanding quadrant of southeast Edmonton and its 60,000 residents within a three kilometer radius, and the city of Beaumont with a population of 18,829.  Anchored by Superstore the 44.56 acre site presents an exciting opportunity for retail, food & beverage and professional tenants of all sizes.  Continued residential growth, high daily traffic counts and ease of access will establish Harvest Hills Market as the premier shopping centre in the region.Harvest Hills Market is located adjacent to Harvest Pointe, a Walmart and Sobeys anchored project, and completes a major retail node for the region.Drive through options available.  Flexible units sizes up to 30,000 sq. ft..159 residential units under construction. Ease of access from two all-directional lit intersections along Ellerslie Road.  Located along the arterial roads of Ellerslie Road and 50th Street, only minutes from Anthony Henday Drive and eight minutes along commuter route to Beaumont.  Seeking all food & beverage, retail and professional uses.  Anticipated Early 2022
